LOCUS       AviTag                    15 aa                     UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  AviTag — a 15-aa synthetic biotin acceptor peptide (GLNDIFEAQKIEWHE)
            that is site-specifically biotinylated on Lys11 (K10 in original
            numbering) by the biotin ligase BirA in vivo or in vitro..
