                     confirmed the optimized 15-mer achieves kcat/Km comparable
                     to the natural BCCP substrate; Lys11 (K10 in original
                     Schatz numbering) is the biotinylation site. Biotinylation
                     is catalyzed by Escherichia coli biotin ligase BirA."
